John 20:1-18\lang9  (ORIGINAL SPACING)\lang1033\par
The Resurrection\par
20 Now on the first day of the week Mary Magdalene came to the tomb early, while it was still dark, and saw that the stone had been taken away from the tomb. 2 So she ran and went to Simon Peter and the other disciple, the one whom Jesus loved, and said to them, \ldblquote They have taken the Lord out of the tomb, and we do not know where they have laid him.\rdblquote  3 So Peter went out with the other disciple, and they were going toward the tomb. 4 Both of them were running together, but the other disciple outran Peter and reached the tomb first. 5 And stooping to look in, he saw the linen cloths lying there, but he did not go in. 6 Then Simon Peter came, following him, and went into the tomb. He saw the linen cloths lying there, 7 and the face cloth, which had been on Jesus' head, not lying with the linen cloths but folded up in a place by itself. 8 Then the other disciple, who had reached the tomb first, also went in, and he saw and believed; 9 for as yet they did not understand the Scripture, that he must rise from the dead. 10 Then the disciples went back to their homes.\par
\par
Jesus Appears to Mary Magdalene\par
11 But Mary stood weeping outside the tomb, and as she wept she stooped to look into the tomb. 12 And she saw two angels in white, sitting where the body of Jesus had lain, one at the head and one at the feet. 13 They said to her, \ldblquote Woman, why are you weeping?\rdblquote  She said to them, \ldblquote They have taken away my Lord, and I do not know where they have laid him.\rdblquote  14 Having said this, she turned around and saw Jesus standing, but she did not know that it was Jesus. 15 Jesus said to her, \ldblquote Woman, why are you weeping? Whom are you seeking?\rdblquote  Supposing him to be the gardener, she said to him, \ldblquote Sir, if you have carried him away, tell me where you have laid him, and I will take him away.\rdblquote  16 Jesus said to her, \ldblquote Mary.\rdblquote  She turned and said to him in Aramaic, \ldblquote Rabboni!\rdblquote  (which means Teacher). 17 Jesus said to her, \ldblquote Do not cling to me, for I have not yet ascended to the Father; but go to my brothers and say to them, \lquote I am ascending to my Father and your Father, to my God and your God.\rquote\rdblquote  18 Mary Magdalene went and announced to the disciples, \ldblquote I have seen the Lord\rdblquote\emdash and that he had said these things to her.\f1\lang9\par
